    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-06-22T09:15:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-06-22T09:15:00-05:00" n="640"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d640">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.61333/824: Airgram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-06-22T11:15:00-03:00"
                            >June 22, 1943—11:15 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 28—4 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A–1310. Reference my airgram A–1174, June 11, 10 a.m.…</p>
                <p>Sr. Valentim Bouças<note n="88" xml:id="d640fn88">Executive Secretary, Commission
                        for the Control of the Washington Agreements.</note> informed the Embassy
                    yesterday that President Vargas has strongly disapproved of Guedes’<note n="89"
                        xml:id="d640fn89">Jayme Fernandes Guedes, President, National Coffee
                        Department.</note> action in increasing <pb facs="0709" n="697"
                        xml:id="pg_697"/> coffee prices following the entry into the market of the
                    United States Quartermaster. Bouças said: “I would not be surprised if President
                    Vargas made a gift of a substantial quantity of coffee to the Armed Forces of
                    the United States Government”.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
